c2epub
======

Where to get c2epub?
--------------------

The c2epub project page is:
http://www.rikiji.it/post/15

Also on GitHub:
http://github.com/rikiji/c2epub


What is c2epub? 
---------------

c2epub is a tool able to generate ebooks in the EPUB format packaging
c source code. It is different from other epub generating software since
default font of generated ebooks is a fixed width one. Blank lines, 
spaces, tabs are preserved and it provides C syntax highlight. You can
choose to package a group of source files together or process them one 
by one creating different epubs.


Who wrote c2epub?
-----------------

EPUB related code is written by Riccardo Cecolin, http://www.rikiji.it
c2epub is based on c2html by Florian Schintke, which provides syntax
highlight and html escaping features.
By using c2epub you are solely responsible for any content that you
create or distribute using c2epub and for the consequences of your
actions by doing so.


How can i use c2epub? 
---------------------

Run it with -h to get the usage help. Default is single output file,
no syntax highlight

usage: c2epub [options] [source files...]
source files have to be in the same directory you run c2epub.
  -t title package title (output filename base)
  -g       enable grayscale
  -m       multiple files output
  -h       print this help
  -v       print version information


Where to get c2html?
--------------------
The homepage of c2html is
http://user.cs.tu-berlin.de/~schintke/x2html/index.html

